{
  "info": {
    "name": "YAWL Engine API v5.2",
    "description": "Enterprise BPM/Workflow Engine REST API Collection\n\n## Overview\nYAWL (Yet Another Workflow Language) provides comprehensive workflow management capabilities through four primary interfaces:\n\n- **Interface A**: Design-time operations (specification upload, validation, management)\n- **Interface B**: Runtime operations (case management, work item execution)\n- **Interface E**: Event and audit logging (process monitoring, compliance)\n- **Interface X**: Extended operations (exception handling, work item control)\n\n## Authentication\nAll endpoints require a valid sessionHandle obtained through the connect endpoint. Sessions expire after one hour of inactivity.\n\n## Usage\n1. Run the 'Connect' request to obtain a session handle\n2. The session handle will be automatically saved to the collection variable\n3. All subsequent requests will use the saved session handle",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "version": "5.2.0"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "noauth"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Auto-set session handle if available",
          "if (pm.collectionVariables.get(\"sessionHandle\")) {",
          "    pm.request.addQueryParam({",
          "        key: \"sessionHandle\",",
          "        value: pm.collectionVariables.get(\"sessionHandle\")",
          "    });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Auto-save session handle from connect response",
          "if (pm.info.requestName === \"Connect\" && pm.response.code === 200) {",
          "    const handle = pm.response.text().trim();",
          "    if (handle && !handle.includes(\"failure\")) {",
          "        pm.collectionVariables.set(\"sessionHandle\", handle);",
          "        console.log(\"Session handle saved:\", handle);",
          "    }",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
